s totally safe it wouldn't surprise me if the anti-nuke freaks still spouted their ignorance against the use of any kind of nuclear propulsion.  If we want to make mass spaceflight and colonization possible I don't think we have an alternative but to develop nuclear propulsion technology.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hamster>Hamster</A> at: 7/8/02 9:18:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cattlecar>cattlecar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 221<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/10/02 1:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=109.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~macami/ez/spinthingie.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/fry1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Opening the Solar-System Frontier - Title: Fusion Propul</span><hr size=1> Anything that uses the 'n' word (nuclear) has a negative impact with the general public.  But at least NASA is learning, in a recent article about advanced propulsion they used the terms fission and fusion instead of the more generic nuclear propulsion.  Nowhere in the article was the word nuclear to be found. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 1638<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/12/02 7:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=109.topic&index=4>Reply</a> 